cmmIIIMibModule.name: cmmIIIMibModule
cmmIIIMibModule.description: This module contains CMM3 MIB definitions.

portNumber.name: portNumber
portNumber.description: A unique value for each CMM port. Its value starts from 1.

rxDropPkts.name: rxDropPkts
rxDropPkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that were dropped due to lack of resources(e.g., lack of input buffers)or were dropped due to lack of resources before a determination of the validity of the packet was able to be made (e.g., receive FIFO overflow). The counter is only incremented if the receive error was not counted by either the RxExcessSizeDisc, the RxAlignmentErrors or the RxRCSErrors counters.

rxOctets.name: rxOctets
rxOctets.description: The number of bytes of data received by a port (excluding preamble but including FCS), including bad packets.

rxBroadcastPkts.name: rxBroadcastPkts
rxBroadcastPkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are directed to the broadcast address. This counter does not include error broadcast packets or valid multicast packets.

rxMulticastPkts.name: rxMulticastPkts
rxMulticastPkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are directed to the multicast address. This counter does not include error multicast packets or valid broadcast packets.

rxSAChanges.name: rxSAChanges
rxSAChanges.description: The number of times the SA of good receive packets has changed from the previous value. A count greater than 1 generally indicates the port if connected to a repeater based network.

rxUndersizePkts.name: rxUndersizePkts
rxUndersizePkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are less than 64 bytes long (excluding framing bits but including the FCS).

rxOversizePkts.name: rxOversizePkts
rxOversizePkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are greater than 1522 bytes inclusive (excluding framing bits but including the FCS). Note that this counter alone will be incremented for packets in the range 1523-1536 bytes inclusive, whereas both this counter and the RxExcessSizeDisc counter will be incremented for packets of 1537 bytes and higher.

rxFragments.name: rxFragments
rxFragments.description: The number of packets received by a port that are less than 64 bytes(excluding framing bits) and have either an FCS error or an alignment error.

rxJabbers.name: rxJabbers
rxJabbers.description: The number of packets received by a port that are longer than 1522 bytes and have either an FCS error or an alignment error.

rxUnicastPkts.name: rxUnicastPkts
rxUnicastPkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are addressed to a unicast address.

rxAlignmentErrors.name: rxAlignmentErrors
rxAlignmentErrors.description: The number of packets received by a port that have a length (excluding framing bits but including FCS) between 64 and 1522 bytes, inclusive, and have a bad FCS with a non-integral number of bytes.

rxFCSErrors.name: rxFCSErrors
rxFCSErrors.description: The number of packets received by a port that have a length (excluding framing bits but including FCS) between 64 and 152 bytes, and have a bad FCS with an integral number of bytes.

rxGoodOctets.name: rxGoodOctets
rxGoodOctets.description: The total number of bytes in all good packets received by a port (excluding framing bits but including FCS).

rxExcessSizeDisc.name: rxExcessSizeDisc
rxExcessSizeDisc.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are greater than 1536 bytes (excluding framing bits but including FCS) and were discarded due to excessive length. Note that the RxOversizePkts counter alone is incremented for packets in the range of 1523-1536 bytes inclusive, whereas both this counter and the RxOversizePkts are incremented for packets of 1537 bytes and higher.

rxPausePkts.name: rxPausePkts
rxPausePkts.description: The number of PAUSE frame received by a port. The PAUSE frame must have a valid MAC Control Frame EtherType field (88-08h), have a destination MAC address of either the MAC Control frame reserved multicast address(01-80-c2-00-00-011) or the unique MAC address associated with the specific port, a valid PAUSE Opcode (00-01), be a minimum of 64 bytes in length (excluding preamble but including FCS), and have a valid CRC. Although an 802.3 compliant MAC is only permitted to transmit PAUSE frames when in full duplex mode, with flow control enabled, and with the transfer of PAUSE frames determined by the result of auto-negotiation, an 802.3 MAC receiver is required to count all received PAUSE frames, regardless of its half/full-duplex status. An indication that a MAC is in half-duplex with the RxPausePkts incrementing indicates a non-compliant transmitting device on the network.

rxSymbolErrors.name: rxSymbolErrors
rxSymbolErrors.description: The total number of times a valid length packet was received at a port and at least one invalid data symbol was detected. Counter only increment once per carrier event and does not increment on detection of collision during the carrier event.

txDropPkts.name: txDropPkts
txDropPkts.description: This counter is incremented every time a transmit packet is dropped due to lack of resources (e.g., transmit FIFO underflow), or an internal MAC sublayer transmit error not counted by in either the TxLateCollision or the TxExcessiveCollision counters.

txOctets.name: txOctets
txOctets.description: The total number of good bytes of data transmitted by a port (excluding preamble but including FCS).

txBroadcastPkts.name: txBroadcastPkts
txBroadcastPkts.description: The number of good packets transmitted by a port that are directed to a broadcast address. This counter does not include errored broadcast packets or valid multicast packets.

txMulticastPkts.name: txMulticastPkts
txMulticastPkts.description: The number of good packets transmitted by a port that are directed to a multicast address. This counter does not include errored multicast packets or valid broadcast packets.

txCollisions.name: txCollisions
txCollisions.description: The number of collision experienced by a port during packet transmissions.

txUnicastPkts.name: txUnicastPkts
txUnicastPkts.description: The number of good packets transmitted by a port that are addressed to a unicast address.

txSingleCollision.name: txSingleCollision
txSingleCollision.description: The number packets successfully transmitted by a port that experienced exactly one collision.

txMultipleCollision.name: txMultipleCollision
txMultipleCollision.description: The number packets successfully transmitted by a port that experienced more than one collision.

txDeferredTransmit.name: txDeferredTransmit
txDeferredTransmit.description: The number packets successfully transmitted by a port for which the first transmission attempt is delayed because medium is busy.

txLateCollision.name: txLateCollision
txLateCollision.description: The number of times that a collision is detected later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet.

txExcessiveCollision.name: txExcessiveCollision
txExcessiveCollision.description: The number of packets that are not transmitted from a port because the packet experienced 16 transmission attempts.

txPausePkts.name: txPausePkts
txPausePkts.description: The number of PAUSE frame transmitted by a port. The MAC resolve to full duplex mode, with 803.3x flow control PAUSE frame exchange enabled at the completion of auto-negotiation.

txFrameInDisc.name: txFrameInDisc
txFrameInDisc.description: The number of valid packets received which are discarded by the forwarding process due to lack of space on an output queue. Note: not maintained or reported in the MIB counters. Located in Congestion registers. This attribute only increments if a network device is not acting in compliance with a flow control request, or the BCM5327M internal flow control/buffering scheme has been misconfigured.

pkts64Octets.name: pkts64Octets
pkts64Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are 64 bytes long.

pkts65to127Octets.name: pkts65to127Octets
pkts65to127Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 65 and 127 bytes long.

pkts128to255Octets.name: pkts128to255Octets
pkts128to255Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 128 and 255 bytes long.

pkts256to511Octets.name: pkts256to511Octets
pkts256to511Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 256 and 511 bytes long.

pkts512to1023Octets.name: pkts512to1023Octets
pkts512to1023Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 512 and 1023 bytes long.

pkts1024to1522Octets.name: pkts1024to1522Octets
pkts1024to1522Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 1024 and 1522 bytes long.

port2PowerCtr.description: Power control for port 2. (1) -- Power on. (0) -- Power off.

displayOnlyAccess.description: Display only access to web interface and telnet.

fullAccess.name: fullAccess
fullAccess.description: Full access password to web interface and telnet.

webAutoUpdate.name: webAutoUpdate
webAutoUpdate.description: Web page auto update in seconds. 0 means disabled.

vlanTagEnable.name: vlanTagEnable
vlanTagEnable.description: Enable/Disable 802.1Q VLAN tagging.P (1) -- Enable Tagging. (0) -- Disable Tagging.

port1Uplink.description: Configure Port 1 as Uplink Port. (1) -- Port 1 is an uplink port. (0) -- Port 1 is not an uplink port.

rebootIfRequired.name: rebootIfRequired
rebootIfRequired.description: Reboot CMM if required. (1) -- Check if CMM reboot is required and do so. (0) -- Do not check for reboot.

port1VlanConf.description: Port 1 VLAN Port Configuration. Bitmap determines which Port(s) Port 1 will egress data. 0 means no ports, 2 means port 2, 6 means ports 2 and 3, etc.
